<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I use Zend_Date to work with Timestamps of DB2.
These timestamps are in text form and look like this: YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.S
Parsing this format works well, but outputting it has an bug with the fractions part:
leading Zeros are left out.
This timestamp '2009-12-29 03:51:21.016145' gets outputted as '2009-12-29 03:51:21.16145',
although the fraction presition is set to 6. I use $date-&gt;toString('YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.S')
for generating the output.</p>

